My meme

This meme is how I started my project just one day before the due date, and it is the first thing that pops into my head when I try to create a meme.

library(magick)

# top left square
weekend_text <-image_blank(width = 200,
                           height = 150,
                           color = "#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "*sleeping on \nweekend",
                color = "#000000",
                size = 30,
                font = "Impact",
                gravity = "center") %>%
  image_blur(100, 1)

# top right square
sleeping_squidward <- image_read("https://i.imgflip.com/2tk0zu.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(400) %>%
  image_crop("200x150", gravity = "northeast")

# bottom left square
project_text <-image_blank(width = 200,
                           height = 150,
                           color = "#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "project 1 \ndue \ntomorrow",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 30,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# bottom right square
awake_squidward <- image_read("https://i.imgflip.com/2tk0zu.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(400) %>%
  image_crop("200x150", gravity = "southeast")

# the top row
top_row <- image_append(c(weekend_text, sleeping_squidward))

# the bottom row
bottom_row <- image_append(c(project_text, awake_squidward))

# put the all together
meme <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

# save the meme
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My animatated GIF

Just a very random GIF to refresh your mind.

library(magick)

# Creating the frames
frame_1 <- image_blank(color = "white", width = 400, height = 400) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "what is the colour \nof the figure", size = 30, gravity = "center")

frame_2 <- image_read("https://www.seekpng.com/png/full/169-1691050_star-shape-star-with-black-background.png") %>%
  image_scale(250) %>%
  image_extent("400x400") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "blue", color = "#0000ff", size = 50, gravity = "center")

frame_3 <- image_read("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/07/Disc_Plain_green_dark.svg/920px-Disc_Plain_green_dark.svg.png?20080329104546") %>%
  image_scale(250) %>%
  image_extent("400x400") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "red", color = "#ff471a", size = 60, gravity = "center")

frame_4 <- image_read("http://clipart-library.com/images/6ip5jXMMT.png") %>%
  image_scale(250) %>%
  image_extent("400x400") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "green", color = "#00ff00", size = 40, gravity = "center")

frame_5 <- image_read("http://clipart-library.com/images/Lcd5AMzri.png") %>%
  image_scale(350) %>%
  image_extent("400x400") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "yellow", color = "#ffff00", size = 40, gravity = "center")

# putting the frames in order
frames <- c(frame_1, frame_2, frame_3, frame_4, frame_5)

animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 1)

# save the GIF
image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
